  Note: this diagnostic completed all responses correctly, but the first
  ad-hoc harness waited on the server process and did not preserve exact
  wall elapsed. Treat it as supporting latency/utilization evidence only.

Decision
--------
Do not promote ready-window slot coalescing. It is correct and default-off,
but the practical 16-slot/256K served A/B is slower than the current per-step
event-handoff baseline. The next throughput attempt should move to a larger
DS4-specific routed-FFN executor boundary or a broader persistent TP/EP
scheduler, not more queue-level slot chunking.
